The paper deals with geometric graph theory and specifically focuses on Yao graphs, which are commonly studied in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses spanners, which are a fundamental concept in distributed computing and network algorithms, making cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also involves analyzing the stretch factor of graphs, which is a common topic in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the L2 and L∞ metrics, which are commonly studied in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
